cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

The paper deals with computer vision and image processing techniques to generate ground-level views from overhead imagery. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with geographic discovery, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics). The use of conditional generative adversarial networks (cGANs) involves machine learning techniques, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the classification of land-cover, which can be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics).
